olved, so we're exploring all possibilities.", "source": "Avoma introductory call 22 Aug 2025 (Florencia Somaini)", "status": "active", "sentiment": "neutral", "how_we_win": "Contrast time-to-value and 25 years of procurement AI patents against a from-scratch build; use the Heineken Merlin reference to show a live, proven outcome the in-house team cannot match quickly.", "threat_level": "medium"}, {"date": "2025-08-22", "name": "Coupa (incumbent P2P platform)", "quote": "We have Coupa since at least 8 years ago... users are completely lost now with Coupa... we are not looking to replace Coupa right now.", "source": "Avoma introductory call 22 Aug 2025 (Florencia Somaini)", "status": "incumbent", "sentiment": "negative", "how_we_win": "Lead with the composable land-and-expand: start on SRM/intake on top of Coupa, prove usability and AI adoption, then earn the P2P conversation after S4HANA settles.", "threat_level": "low"}, {"date": "2025-08-22", "name": "Salesforce supplier-connect (incumbent SRM tool being displaced)", "quote": "for supplier management we have Salesforce... it's not a real supplier management tool... yes, we are looking to maybe replace it.", "source": "Avoma introductory call 22 Aug 2025 (Florencia Somaini)", "status": "incumbent", "sentiment": "negative", "how_we_win": "This is the beachhead: position iSupplier plus iRisk as the purpose-built replacement for the Salesforce workaround, with risk and performance unified in one place.", "threat_level": "low"}, {"date": "2025-08-22", "name": "SAP Ariba (incumbent sourcing)", "quote": "for sourcing we are using Ariba... a very long time.", "source": "Avoma introductory call 22 Aug 2025 (Florencia Somaini)", "status": "incumbent", "sentiment": "neutral", "how_we_win": "Out of scope for the SRM beachhead; note as future displacement once Zycus is proven, do not compete on it now.", "threat_level": "dormant"}, {"date": "2025-08-22", "name": "Keelvar (logistics sourcing, expanding)", "quote": "we started to use Keelvar for logistics, and now we are expanding the use of Keelvar within the company for other categories.", "source": "Avoma introductory call 22 Aug 2025 (Florencia Somaini)", "status": "incumbent", "sentiment": "neutral", "how_we_win": "Not competing for SRM scope; monitor its category expansion so it does not pre-empt future Zycus sourcing scope.", "threat_level": "dormant"}]}, "champion_strength": {"source": "SF Contact Roles; Avoma call 22 Aug 2025; SF Next_Step__c 24 Oct 2025 and 1 April 2026", "at_risk": true, "summary": "Florencia Somaini is a developing champion whose advocacy is real (drove the conversation, well-received Oct 2025 demo, Horizon attendance, positive April email) but who has not developed the ability to multi-thread or reach budget authority, and has now gone quiet for about 93 days after promising to align internally. What is still missing: an economic-buyer introduction, a broader stakeholder group, and any budget or timeline commitment.", "champion": "Florencia Somaini", "strength": "developing"}, "stakeholder_map": {"items": [{"name": "Florencia Somaini", "risk": "Operational, lacks budget authority and has not delivered on her 1 April promise to involve broader stakeholders; if she stays the only thread the deal cannot progress.", "role": "Champion", "email": "florencia.somaini@frieslandcampina.com", "title": "Procurement Excellence Manager", "_source": "sfdc_contact_role", "sentiment": "Positive but cooling; genuine advocate leading the digital-procurement roadmap, but silent about 93 days and unable to mobilize a broader group or budget.", "_matched_ai": true, "last_contact_date": "2026-04-01"}, {"name": "Jean-Olivier QUENTIN", "risk": "Most senior procurement leader on the record yet completely unmapped; without his (or a peer's) sponsorship there is no budget path.", "role": "Economic Buyer", "email": "jean-olivier.quentin@frieslandcampina.com", "title": "Global Director, Procurement & Chief People Officer", "_source": "sfdc_contact_role", "sentiment": "Unknown; named in contact roles but never engaged on any call or activity.", "_matched_ai": true}, {"name": "Felipe Brollo", "risk": "Never engaged; a credible economic buyer left untouched.", "role": "Economic Buyer", "email": "felipe.brollo@frieslandcampina.com", "title": "Global Indirects Procurement Director", "_source": "sfdc_contact_role", "sentiment": "Unknown; in contact roles, never engaged; SRM sits under indirects so a natural budget owner.", "_matched_ai": true}, {"name": "Nauman Malik", "risk": "Owns the transformation agenda that is currently freezing the deal; leaving him unmapped keeps the S4HANA objection unaddressed.", "role": "Influencer", "email": "nauman.malik@frieslandcampina.com", "title": "Head of Procurement Sourcing & Expertise Global- GPO & Transformation Lead", "_source": "sfdc_contact_role", "sentiment": "Unknown; transformation remit makes him pivotal to the S4HANA-versus-new-tooling decision, but never engaged.", "_matched_ai": true}, {"name": "Vincent Bremond", "risk": "A newly opened thread that has not responded; a potential second entry point if activated.", "role": "Influencer", "email": "vincent.bremond@frieslandcampina.com", "title": "Head of Specialties - Global Category Procurement", "_source": "sfdc_contact_role", "sentiment": "Unknown; recently targeted by a rep roundtable invitation, no reply yet.", "_matched_ai": true, "last_contact_date": "2026-05-21"}, {"name": "Turgut Taghizade", "risk": "Passive peer to Florencia with no evidence of power access; supportive but not a mover.", "role": "Influencer", "email": "turgut.taghizade@frieslandcampina.com", "title": "Global Procurement Excellence Manager", "_source": "sfdc_contact_role", "sentiment": "Neutral; attended the 24 Oct 2025 demo with Florencia, no further engagement.", "_matched_ai": true, "last_contact_date": "2025-10-24"}, {"name": "Vincent Klomp", "role": "Decision Maker", "email": "vincent.klomp@frieslandcampina.com", "title": "Head of Procurement Thailand | Regional MRO & FM Lead, Asia", "_source": "sfdc_contact_role", "_role_inferred": true}, {"name": "Rutger Burger", "role": "Influencer", "email": "rutger.burger@frieslandcampina.com", "title": "Director Business Procurement", "_source": "sfdc_contact_role", "_role_inferred": true}]}, "meddpicc": {"metrics": {"status": "partial", "sources": ["Avoma introductory call 22 Aug 2025 (Florencia Somaini)", "SF Products__c"], "narrative": "The pain is well articulated but never quantified into a savings or ROI case. On the 22 Aug 2025 introductory call Florencia Somaini described roughly 2.4 billion in annual spend, an expanding set of buying channels and users 'completely lost' trying to find the right buying channel in Coupa, plus a fragmented tool estate (Coupa for P2P, SAP Ariba and Keelvar for sourcing, Salesforce for supplier management which she called 'not a real supplier management tool'). No cost, cycle-time or headcount number was attached to any of this, and the effort was framed as exploratory ('we are just exploring'). Quantifying the SRM business case against the 2.4 billion spend is the move."}, "champion": {"status": "partial", "sources": ["SF Next_Step__c 24 Oct 2025 and 1 April 2026", "Avoma introductory call 22 Aug 2025", "SF Contact Roles (Florencia Somaini)"], "narrative": "Florencia Somaini is a genuine but stalling champion. She initiated and drove the conversation, brings 15 years of procurement-tech and Coupa implementation experience (a credible cross-platform comparator), attended the 24 Oct 2025 SRM and Merlin Intake demo which was 'well received', accepted the Horizon invitation and on 1 April 2026 wrote that it was 'valuable to continue the conversation and involve a broader group of stakeholders'. What has NOT developed is her ability to mobilize: 93 days after promising to align internally she has not reverted, has not introduced any economic buyer, and lacks budget authority. She is a developing, now-cooling champion w